1. A filtration system comprising:
a channel having an inlet and an outlet;
a membrane positioned within the channel between the inlet and the outlet; and
a controller configured to cycle a flow of a volume of fluid based on a volumetric flow ratio from flowing in a forward direction through the membrane at a volume of fluid flow Vf, to flowing in a reverse direction through the membrane at a volume of fluid flow Vr;
wherein the forward direction of fluid flow is from the inlet, through the membrane, and to the outlet;
wherein the reverse direction of fluid flow is from the outlet, through the membrane, and to the inlet; and
wherein the volumetric flow ratio is equal to


\(\frac{V_{f}}{V_{f} + V_{r}}.\)

2. A filtration system comprising:
a channel having an inlet and an outlet;
a membrane positioned within the channel between the inlet and the outlet;
a suspension comprising a fluid, first particles, and second particles, the mean size of the first particles larger the mean size of the second particles; and
a controller configured to cycle a flow of a volume of the suspension based on a volumetric flow ratio from flowing in a forward direction through the membrane at a volume of flow Vf, to flowing in a reverse direction through the membrane at a volume of flow Vr;
wherein the forward direction of suspension flow is from the inlet, through the membrane, and to the outlet;
wherein the reverse direction of suspension flow is from the outlet, through the membrane, and to the inlet; and
wherein the membrane is configured to allow at least a portion of the fluid and a portion of the second particles of the suspension flowing in the forward direction to permeate through the membrane; and
wherein the membrane is configured to prevent at least a portion of the first particles of the suspension flowing in the forward direction to permeate through the membrane.

8. The system of claim 2, wherein the volumetric flow ratio is from between 0.5 and 1.00;
wherein the controller is further configured to vary at least one of volume of flow Vf and volume of flow Vr from a first cycle to a subsequent second cycle; and
wherein in at least one of the cycles, the volume of flow Vf and volume of flow Vr are not the same.

18. The filtration system of claim 1, wherein the inlet is configured to receive a suspension, the suspension comprising the fluid, first particles, and second particles; and
wherein the controller is further configured to monitor an amount of the second particles permeating through the membrane during flow in the forward direction of a first cycle, and based on the monitored amount, vary during a subsequent second cycle at least one of:
the volumetric flow ratio;
the flow rate in the forward direction;
the flow rate in the reverse direction;
a duration of flow in the forward direction; and
a duration of flow in the reversion direction.

35. The method of claim 19 further comprising:
monitoring an amount of the second particles permeating through the membrane during flow of the fluid in the forward direction of a first cycle; and
varying during a subsequent second cycle, based on the monitored amount, at least one of:
the volumetric flow ratio;
the flow rate in the forward direction;
the flow rate in the reverse direction;
a duration of flow in the forward direction; and
a duration of flow in the reversion direction.

37. The method of claim 19, wherein the volumetric flow ratio has a linear relationship to a recovery percentage for a portion of the second particles permeating through the membrane, the method further comprising:
calculating the recovery percentage of the second particles permeating through the membrane at a plurality of volumetric flow ratios;
identifying a desired permeation amount for a portion of the second particles based on the recovery percentage;
calculating a desired volumetric flow ratio based on the linear relationship;
adjusting the volumetric flow ratio to equal the desired volumetric flow ratio; and
recovering the desired permeation amount for the portion of the second particles.

38. A method of controlling seed density and uniformity comprising:
cycling the suspension through the filtration system of claim 2;
wherein the filtration system comprises a profusion bioreactor;
wherein the membrane comprises a tissue scaffold; and
wherein the first and second particles are cells.
